1
00:00:18,818 --> 00:00:19,919
I can do it too.

2
00:00:25,325 --> 00:00:26,993
But you should smile more.

3
00:00:27,227 --> 00:00:28,862
You've always got such a long face.

4
00:00:30,063 --> 00:00:31,223
Is this "persona" of yours...

5
00:00:31,264 --> 00:00:32,824
something your manager came up with?

6
00:00:33,733 --> 00:00:34,534
I really don't get...

7
00:00:34,535 --> 00:00:36,375
why you signed with
him in the first place.

8
00:00:38,471 --> 00:00:40,105
I tried looking you up,

9
00:00:40,106 --> 00:00:42,007
but there's hardly any info out there.

10
00:00:42,008 --> 00:00:43,008
There's not much to tell.

11
00:00:44,277 --> 00:00:45,644
I read an interview that said...

12
00:00:45,645 --> 00:00:48,047
you joined the industry
because of someone.

13
00:00:48,048 --> 00:00:49,816
Did they just like celebrities,

14
00:00:51,418 --> 00:00:52,318
or were they an artist too?

15
00:00:52,318 --> 00:00:54,373
Are you just so used to this
that you're not afraid of anything?

16
00:01:02,328 --> 00:01:03,063
Sorry...

17
00:01:03,063 --> 00:01:03,663
That car in the other lane...

18
00:01:03,663 --> 00:01:04,663
just cut me off.

19
00:01:06,566 --> 00:01:08,268
It's okay. Just take it slow.

20
00:01:09,002 --> 00:01:10,002
We're in no rush.

21
00:01:10,437 --> 00:01:11,437
It's fine.

22
00:01:12,005 --> 00:01:13,005
Really, it's okay.

23
00:01:16,543 --> 00:01:17,811
Are you babying me?

24
00:01:18,912 --> 00:01:20,213
That's a first.

25
00:01:21,981 --> 00:01:23,449
That car accident you had...

26
00:01:23,450 --> 00:01:24,851
was it really bad?

27
00:01:25,318 --> 00:01:26,352
Did it leave a scar?

28
00:01:27,087 --> 00:01:28,087
Let me see.

29
00:01:33,860 --> 00:01:35,340
Let's save that for when we're alone.

30
00:01:38,832 --> 00:01:39,466
By the way,

31
00:01:39,467 --> 00:01:40,499
have you seen that...

32
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:42,302
"Black &amp; White" fan group?

33
00:01:43,670 --> 00:01:44,670
What about it?

34
00:01:45,405 --> 00:01:47,005
It seems like...

35
00:01:47,006 --> 00:01:48,575
a lot of people are shipping it now.

36
00:01:50,810 --> 00:01:52,011
And do you ship it?

37
00:01:53,012 --> 00:01:54,747
I didn't at first,

38
00:01:55,942 --> 00:01:57,862
but after spending these
last two days together,

39
00:01:58,251 --> 00:01:59,252
it actually seems okay.

40
00:02:01,921 --> 00:02:02,921
But still,

41
00:02:03,189 --> 00:02:04,690
you have so many "girlfriend fans"...

42
00:02:04,691 --> 00:02:06,251
aren't you afraid they'll jump ship?

43
00:02:07,927 --> 00:02:08,994
No matter how many fans I have,

44
00:02:08,995 --> 00:02:10,296
they can't compete with you.

45
00:02:12,398 --> 00:02:13,866
Whoever gets to be your girlfriend...

46
00:02:13,867 --> 00:02:14,834
must be so lucky.

47
00:02:14,835 --> 00:02:16,536
Being my boyfriend is pretty great, too.

48
00:02:20,740 --> 00:02:22,574
Alright, look at you being so talkative.

49
00:02:22,575 --> 00:02:24,544
Were you worried I'd be anxious in the car?

50
00:02:24,944 --> 00:02:25,944
I'm fine.

51
00:02:26,412 --> 00:02:27,572
Why don't you get some sleep?
